                    <msContents>
                        <summary>The third volume of a five-volume set containing stories from the
                            Arabian Nights and other sources.</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="manuscript_13836-item1">
                            <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_700">Alf laylah
                                wa-laylah</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ar">الف ليلة وليلة؛ حكاية جرت بين هارون الرشيد وباسم
                                الحداد؛ خبر الملك كلعاد مع شيماس الحكيم وما جرى لهم بالبيان</title>
                            <title xml:lang="en" type="supplied">A Thousand and One Nights</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                            <note><p>For the other volumes of the set, see <ref
                                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_13834"
                                        >Arabic MS 134</ref> (Vol. 1), <ref
                                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_13835"
                                        >Arabic MS 135</ref> (Vol. 2), <ref
                                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_13837"
                                        >Arabic MS 137</ref> (Vol. 4), <ref
                                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_13838"
                                        >Arabic MS 138</ref> (Vol. 5).</p></note>
                            <msItem xml:id="Arabic_MS_136-item1-item1">
                                <locus from="1" to="65"/>
                                <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Ḥikāyat jarat bayn Hārūn al-Rashīd
                                    wa-Bāsim al-ḥidād</title>
                                <title xml:lang="ar">حكاية جرت بين هارون الرشيد وباسم الحداد</title>
                                <note><p>The story of Bāsim the smith, in connection with the Caliph
                                        Hārūn al-Rashīd who (for fun), on four occasions,
                                        unsuccessfully tried to stop his income
                                    (Mingana).</p></note>
                            </msItem>

                            <msItem xml:id="Arabic_MS_136-item1-item2">
                                <locus from="66" to="157"/>
                                <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc"/>
                                <title xml:lang="ar">جير الملك كلعاد مع شيماس الحكيم وما جرى لهم
                                    بالبيان</title>
                                <note><p>The story of the King Galaʿād and the philosopher Shīmās
                                        (Mingana).</p></note>
                            </msItem>
                        </msItem>
